<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
Monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grote" authorityYear="1895" box="[429,535,1778,1802]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rivulinae">Rivulinae</taxonomicName>
is supported by eight synapomorphies (
<bibRefCitation author="Costa WJEM" box="[339,497,1810,1834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="233 - 49" refId="ref13755" refString="Costa WJEM. Phylogenetic position and taxonomic status of Anablepsoides, Atlantirivulus, Cynodonichthys, Laimosemion, and Melanorivulus (Cyprinodontiformes: Rivulidae). Ichthyol Explor Freshw. 2011 a; 22 (3): 233 - 49." type="journal article" year="2011">Costa, 2011a</bibRefCitation>
): 1. ventral process of the angulo-articular narrow and triangular shaped (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[129,168,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[203,1390,1483,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[185,1394,1478,1859]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Lower jaw of a. Kryptolebias brasiliensis (modified from Costa, 2004), b. Pterolebias longipinnis, c. Papiliolebiass bitteri, d. Cynopoecilus melanotaenia, e. Austrolebias juanlangi, f. Austrolebias wolterstorffi; aad = anguloarticular dorsal process, aav = anguloarticular ventral process, d = dentary, r = retroarticular. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3709845" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3709845/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
b-c); 2. interhyal bone rudimentary or absent; 3. first epibranchial twisted (
<figureCitation box="[377,460,1906,1930]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[136,175,673,697]" captionTargetBox="[188,1424,182,647]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[163,1433,174,657]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Ventral view of dorsal gill arches of a. Pterolebias longipinnis, b. Cynopoecilus melanotaenia, c. Austrolebias juanlangi; e = epibranchial series, ph = pharyngobranchial series, spe2 = epibranchial subdistal process, upe3 = uncinate process of epibranchial 3. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3709847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3709847/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
); 4. subdistal process of the second epibranchial absent (
<figureCitation box="[454,538,1938,1962]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[136,175,673,697]" captionTargetBox="[188,1424,182,647]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[163,1433,174,657]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Ventral view of dorsal gill arches of a. Pterolebias longipinnis, b. Cynopoecilus melanotaenia, c. Austrolebias juanlangi; e = epibranchial series, ph = pharyngobranchial series, spe2 = epibranchial subdistal process, upe3 = uncinate process of epibranchial 3. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3709847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3709847/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
); 5. uncinate process of the third epibranchial forming an angle of about 45–60° (
<figureCitation box="[828,910,208,233]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[136,175,673,697]" captionTargetBox="[188,1424,182,647]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[163,1433,174,657]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Ventral view of dorsal gill arches of a. Pterolebias longipinnis, b. Cynopoecilus melanotaenia, c. Austrolebias juanlangi; e = epibranchial series, ph = pharyngobranchial series, spe2 = epibranchial subdistal process, upe3 = uncinate process of epibranchial 3. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3709847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3709847/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
); 6. paired process on the first vertebra anteriorly directed; 7. membrane between preopercular laterosensory series and isthmus continuous; 8. E-scales not overlapped. Other combined (
<bibRefCitation author="Costa WEJM" box="[1011,1147,305,329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="139 - 54" refId="ref13870" refString="Costa WEJM. Historical biogeography of Aplocheiloid killifishes (Teleostei: Cyprinodontiformes). Vertebr Zool. 2013; 63 (2): 139 - 54." type="journal article" year="2013">Costa, 2013</bibRefCitation>
); and molecular phylogenies (
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy WJ &amp; Collier GE" box="[827,1076,336,360]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="642 - 49" refId="ref16007" refString="Murphy WJ, Collier GE. Phylogenetic relationships within the aplocheiloid fish genus Rivulus (Cyprinodontiformes, Rivulidae): Implications for Caribbean and Central American biogeography. Mol Biol Evol. 1996; 13 (5): 642 - 49." type="journal article" year="1996">Murphy, Collier, 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy WJ &amp; Thomerson, JE &amp; Collier GE" box="[1088,1310,336,361]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="289 - 301" refId="ref16093" refString="Murphy WJ, Thomerson, JE, Collier GE. Phylogeny of the Neotropical killifish family Rivulidae (Cyprinodontiformes, Aplocheiloidei) inferred from mitochondrial DNA sequences. Mol Phylogenet Evol. 1999; 13 (2): 289 - 301." type="journal article" year="1999">
Murphy 
<emphasis box="[1183,1231,336,360]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
., 1999
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hrbek T &amp; Deus CP &amp; Farias IP" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="569 - 76" refId="ref15245" refString="Hrbek T, Deus CP, Farias IP. Rivulus duckensis (Teleostei; Cyprinodontiformes): New species from the Taruma basin of Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil, and its relationships to other Neotropical Rivulidae. Copeia. 2004; (3): 569 - 76." type="journal article" year="2004">
Hrbek 
<emphasis box="[1397,1445,336,360]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
., 2004
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vermeulen FBN &amp; Hrbek T" box="[890,1163,368,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref16864" refString="Vermeulen FBN, Hrbek T. Kryptolebias sepia n. sp. (Actinopterygii: Cyprinodontiformes: Rivulidae), a new killifish from the Tapanahony River drainage in southeast Surinam. Zootaxa. 2005; 928 (1): 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="2005">Vermeulen, Hrbek, 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Furness AI &amp; Reznick DN &amp; Springer MS &amp; Meredith RW" box="[1175,1397,368,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="20142189" refId="ref14726" refString="Furness AI, Reznick DN, Springer MS, Meredith RW. Convergent evolution of alternative developmental trajectories associated with diapause in African and South American killifish. Proc R Soc B Biol Sci. 2015; 282 (1802): 20142189." type="journal article" year="2015">
Furness 
<emphasis box="[1268,1317,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
., 2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl M &amp; Milvertz FC &amp; Meyer A &amp; Vences M" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="37 - 44" refId="ref16484" refString="Pohl M, Milvertz FC, Meyer A, Vences M. Multigene phylogeny of Cyprinodontiform fishes suggests continental rediations and a rogue taxon position of Pantanodon. Vertebr Zool. 2015; 65 (1): 37 - 44." type="journal article" year="2015">
Pohl 
<emphasis box="[820,868,400,424]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
., 2015
</bibRefCitation>
) support the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grote" authorityYear="1895" box="[1249,1359,400,424]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rivulinae">Rivulinae</taxonomicName>
</subSubSection>
.
